description:
&lt;p&gt;CARE PLUS GROUP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cambridge Park&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy based at Cambridge Park, Peterhouse Road, Grimsby&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference Number: 814-20-190&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range 5 £24,554 - £29,912 pro rata per annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week – both full time and part time options available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent posts which include weekend and Bank Holiday working on a planned rota basis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Plus Group is a Social Enterprise established since 2011 to deliver community healthcare services following the national separation of provider services from the commissioning arm of the local NHS. One of our core values is that staff and patients are integral to everything we do. As part of this all staff employed by Care Plus Group automatically become members of the Group which means you will be able to give your views and vote on important issues for the organisation. We welcome your application to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridge Park is a new Enhanced Recovery Facility within North East Lincolnshire offering a number of wonderful opportunities for professionals to join the newly established team. The focus of Cambridge Park is to deliver our Enhanced Recovery Model by way of encouragement and enablement delivering Intensive Therapy and Nursing focussing on achieving the best possible outcomes for the patients we support, both during their stay with us and also when they leave us and return home. At Cambridge Park the team are made up of Allied Health Professionals, Nursing, Social Work and Skilled Non-Registered Staff all contributing to the multi-disciplinary approach enabling the most effective delivery and Enhanced Recovery to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit experienced Nurses to work with us at Cambridge Park as key members of our multi-disciplinary team. Our Nurses will work in partnership with the multi-disciplinary team supporting interventions with our patients with a focus on always achieving the best outcomes for them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a Registered Nurse educated to Degree Level and have current NMC Registration. We are looking for experienced nurses who have acute clinical examination and assessment skills and have the ability to receive, interpret and act on complex information and being able to act on own judgement and decision making. Previous experience of working as part of a multi-disciplinary team would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and an informal discussion please contact &lt;strong&gt;Helen Leary (Manager)&lt;/strong&gt;on &lt;strong&gt;07717 693636.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLOSING DATE: 15 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for more information, and the criteria required to fulfil the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that any offer of a post is subject to pre-employment screening. The offer will also be provisional upon receipt of a satisfactory &lt;strong&gt;Enhanced &lt;/strong&gt;DBS check, of which the successful candidate will be responsible for payment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer favourable terms and conditions including optional membership to a contributory pension scheme, lease cars, a full induction programme and CPD opportunities. We have Independent Provider closed access to the NHS pension scheme, for further details about eligibility please contact us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Plus Group will interview all disabled candidates who meet the minimum criteria for any job vacancy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that if you have not heard from us within 6 weeks of the closing date we regret that you have not been short listed on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Plus Group is an equal opportunities employer. It is our Policy to provide and ensure equal opportunities in the fields of recruitment, employment, training, promotion and job security irrespective of any characteristics which may place an applicant in any minority or disadvantaged group or groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to safeguarding the welfare of vulnerable adults and expect the same commitment from all staff and volunteers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
